<doc id="471022" wikidata="Q5593811" url="?curid=471022" title="Grammy Award for Best Gospel Vocal Performance by a Duo or Group, Choir or Chorus">
<text>The Grammy Award for Best Gospel Vocal Performance by a Duo or Group, Choir or Chorus was awarded from 1984 to 1990. The award was originally titled Best Gospel Performance by a Duo or Group. This was changed to Best Gospel Performance by a Duo or Group, Choir or Chorus in 1986 and &quot;Vocal&quot; was added in 1990.

Years reflect the year in which the Grammy Awards were presented, for works released in the previous year.

